<li>
<a href="article.cfm?id=3310318">Silence is golden, especially when you need to say something important</a><br />
<div class="by_line">
by
Philip Yaffe
<br>
February 2019
</div>
<div>
<p>Each "Communication Corner" essay is self-contained; however, they build on each other. For best results, before reading this essay and doing the exercise, go to the first essay "How an Ugly Duckling Became a Swan," then read each succeeding essay.</p> <p>How well you speak will always be an indicator of how well you know the subject at hand. And while nerves can often lead novice speakers to resort to distracting sounds and placeholders, a second or two of silence will help focus you as well as your audience. In this installment, Philip Yaffe reminds us that silence is golden.</p>
