<div class="by_line">
by
Philip Yaffe
<br>
March 2016
</div>
<div>
<p>Science depends on logical reasoning. However, the conclusions one comes to intimately depend on the explicit, or more often implicit, assumptions on which the reasoning is based. Here is an example of how logical reasoning based on different assumptions can lead to diametrically opposite conclusions.</p>
