<li>
<a href="article.cfm?id=2447479">Ubiquity symposium: The science in computer science: the sixteen character traits of science</a><br />
<div class="by_line">
by
Philip Yaffe
<br>
March 2013
</div>
<div>
<p>Phil Yaffe has provided numerous commentaries on various aspects of professional communication, which have helped readers more effectively articulate their own ideas about the future of computing. Here he tells us about how scientists see the world---the "scientific approach," he calls it---because he thinks many non-scientists see the world in a similar way. This realization can lower barriers of communication with scientists.</p>
<a href="index.cfm?page=article&id=2447479">
<a href="article.cfm?id=2447479">...</a>
</div>
